This article is a transcript of remarks made by President Donald Trump on September 26, 2019. The President discusses the changes his administration has made in communities across the country, including progress on the border. He thanks the President of Mexico for the assistance in guarding the border and mentions that 27,000 Mexican soldiers are currently stationed there. The President criticizes the Democrats for their unwillingness to change loopholes and asylum laws, accusing them of wanting open borders, crime, drugs, and human trafficking. Sheriff Hodgson expresses his appreciation for the President's leadership and efforts to stop illegal immigration. The President is presented with a plaque of recognition by America's sheriffs. He thanks them for their support and emphasizes that his administration has done more for safety and security in the last two and a half years than the previous 20 years of administrations.